    Page: 828-829
Tags:
  - 828
By: Ibn'Arabi
---
God is the mirror in which thou seest thyself, as thou art His mirror in
which He contemplates His Names; now these are nothing other than Himself,
in such a way that the analogy of the relationship is inverse.
